	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm known as the Dress Wearing Tank.<br><br>52 Wizzie with crud AC (480 ish) and lame HP (Arch Shielding is needed to get me over 1000, up to 1070 ish)<br>But H2H is at 44, and all melee weaps skills are maxed (110).<br>Just because sometimes you really want to get personal with a mob and just hit it with a stick.<br>A snared Ice Giant under 19pct health will stand stationary while you beat it up, and with C3 or higher, by the time he dies, I am back up to 80pct mana, even after snaring again.<br>Now that I know of this charm, I want, I want, I want.&nbsp;&nbsp;I think it was made for casters like me.  Maybe even more so than the Charm of Solitude I had been craving for.<br><br>Melee is not the job of a caster, but it's a game. Have fun any way you can.  And knife fights are great fun!<br><br>No, I do not think it is worth maxing your skills for this charm, unless it is the only charm you have managed to find.  There are better charms about.  But if you are already maxed like myself, this is great !<br><br>If you really want to increase your skills, get a shammy to help you with Dex and Haste.<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Apr 22 23:00:52 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Opy<br><br>EverQuest - Not so much a game, as a chat site,<br>with swords.</td></tr>
